title: Presidential vote heading toward a runoff election in Argentina
text: Presidential vote heading toward a runoff election in Argentina BUENOS AIRES, Argentina — The leading opposition candidate in Argentina’s presidential election took a razor-thin lead over President Cristina Fernandez’s chosen successor early Monday, a surprise that months of national polls failed to anticipate. With 72 percent of polling places reporting from Sunday’s election, Mauricio Macri had 36 percent of the votes, compared to 35 percent for ruling party candidate Daniel Scioli. Fernandez sharply increased spending on social welfare programs, which range from work training to stipends for single mothers. ...
